THE DISNEY STORE

THE COMPANY MARKETS DISNEY-THEMED

PRODUCTS DIRECTLY THROUGH RETAIL STORES OPERATED UNDER THE DISNEY STORE NAME. THESE FACILITIES ARE GENERALLY LOCATED IN LEADING SHOPPING MALLS AND OTHER RETAIL COMPLEXES. THE STORES CARRY A WIDE VARIETY OF DISNEY MERCHANDISE AND PROMOTE OTHER

BUSINESSES OF THE COMPANY. THE COMPANY OWNS AND OPERATES 105 STORES IN EUROPE. IN JAPAN, THE STORES ARE OPERATED BY A SUBSIDIARY OF ORIENTAL LAND CO., LTD., UNDER A LICENSING ARRANGEMENT. IN FISCAL 2005, 315 STORES IN NORTH AMERICA WERE SOLD TO A

WHOLLY-OWNED SUBSIDIARY OF THE CHILDRENS PLACE, WHICH OPERATES THEM UNDER A LICENSING AND OPERATING ARRANGEMENT. AT SEPTEMBER 29, 2007, THE CHILDRENS PLACE OPERATED 328 STORES UNDER THIS ARRANGEMENT. SEE NOTE 3 TO THE CONSOLIDATED

FINANCIAL STATEMENTS FOR DISCUSSION ON THE SALE OF THE DISNEY STORE CHAIN IN NORTH AMERICA.

