DURING FISCAL 2007, THE COMPANY RECEIVED $1.5 BILLION IN PROCEEDS FROM THE SALES OF OUR INTERESTS IN E! ENTERTAINMENT TELEVISION AND US WEEKLY, WHICH WAS PARTIALLY OFFSET BY PAYMENTS FOR ACQUISITIONS DRIVEN BY THE

